  "type": "class",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Sentinels are unique in bringing both tech and biotic abilities to the battlefield.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Hit Die:&nbsp;</strong>d10</li>\n<li><strong>Primary Ability:&nbsp;</strong>Charisma</li>\n<li><strong>Saves:&nbsp;</strong>Charisma &amp; Constitution</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"tactical-focus\" style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 800; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 0.458cm; line-height: inherit; font-family: MrJeeves; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #58180d;\">Tactical Focus</h4>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid;\">At 3rd level, your tactical acumen and predictive VI algorithms allow you to provide direction to your allies that can tilt a battle in your favor.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: -0.8em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\">As a bonus action, you can select an area within 30m on the ground that measures 6m on each side. This area is your tactical focus. It remains your tactical focus until you use this ability again or you become&nbsp;.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: -0.8em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\">When you select an area as your tactical focus, you choose one of your tactics to apply to that area. You gain three tactics at 3rd level. You gain an additional tactic at 7th and 14th level. Each time you complete a long rest, you can swap one of your tactics for a different one.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: -0.8em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\">Additionally, at 7th level the size of your tactical focus becomes 8m on each side. At 14th level the size becomes 10m on each side.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: -0.8em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h4 id=\"tactics\" style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 800; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 0.458cm; line-height: inherit; font-family: MrJeeves; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #58180d;\">Tactics</h4>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid;\">Choose from the following tactics.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: -0.8em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\"><strong style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">Advance</strong>. Update your allies' HUDs and outline optimal routes to your tactical focus. If an ally spends all of its movement moving towards your tactical focus, it doubles its movement, ignores difficult terrain, and does not provoke attacks of opportunity.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: -0.8em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\"><strong style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">Analysis</strong>. Focus all of your attention on the movements and capabilities of a single enemy. When you choose this tactic, you additionally choose a single hostile creature within your tactical focus. Beginning when you set your tactical focus and at the beginning of each of your subsequent turns, the DM tells you if the creature is your equal, superior, or inferior in regard to one of the following characteristics of your choice: One ability score (Strength, Dexterity, Constitution, Intelligence, Charisma, or Wisdom), Armor Class, or Current hit points</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: -0.8em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\"><strong style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">Clear the area</strong>. Pick out weak spots on your targets that force them out of your tactical focus. If an ally hit s a creature in your tactical focus with a weapon attack, the ally can move that creature 2m.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: -0.8em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\"><strong style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">Heads up</strong>. If an allied creature in your tactical focus must make a Dexterity saving throw it has advantage on that saving throw.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: -0.8em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\"><strong style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">Pin down</strong>. When a hostile creature attempts to move out of your tactical focus, two target creatures of your choice can use a reaction to make an attack of opportunity on the target. If both attacks are successful, the creature's movement becomes 0, it falls prone and remains in your tactical focus.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: -0.8em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\"><strong style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">Recon</strong>. Your VI focuses on the movement of dust and augments sound from your area of focus, reconstructing a perfect image on your and your allies' HUD. Any creature within your tactical focus loses any benefits from being invisible, lightly obscured, or heavily obscured.</p>\n<h4 id=\"master-tactician\" style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 800; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 0.458cm; line-height: inherit; font-family: MrJeeves; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #58180d;\">Master Tactician</h4>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid;\">At 3rd level, you can use the Help action as a bonus action. Additionally, when you use the Help action to aid an ally in attacking a creature, the target of that attack can be within 20m of you, rather than 2m of you, if the target can see or hear you.</p>\n<h4 id=\"ever-ready\" style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 800; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 0.458cm; line-height: inherit; font-family: MrJeeves; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #58180d;\">Ever Ready</h4>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid;\">By 7th level, you've learned to never let your guard down. You have advantage on initiative rolls.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: -0.8em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\">Additionally, if you are surprised at the beginning of combat and aren't incapacitated, you can act normally on your first turn, but only if you activate your tactical focus, selecting an area that encompasses your location, before doing anything else on that turn.</p>\n<h4 id=\"call-the-shots\" style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 800; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 0.458cm; line-height: inherit; font-family: MrJeeves; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #58180d;\">Call the Shots</h4>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid;\">Starting at 10th level, you can use your action to focus all of your attention on your tactical focus, calling out threats, troop movements, and enemy weaknesses.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: -0.8em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\">Until the start of your next turn:</p>\n<ul style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.8em; padding-left: 1.4em; list-style-position: outside; list-style-image: initial;\">\n<li style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; break-inside: avoid;\">Whenever a friendly creature makes an attack roll or saving throw, it rolls 1d6 and adds the result to its attack roll or saving throw.</li>\n<li style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; break-inside: avoid;\">Whenever a hostile creature makes an attack roll or saving throw, it rolls 1d6 and subtracts the result to its attack roll or saving throw.</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\">You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Charisma modifier (a minimum of once). You regain any expended uses when you finish a long rest.</p>\n<h4 id=\"tactical-maneuvers\" style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 800; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 0.458cm; line-height: inherit; font-family: MrJeeves; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #58180d;\">Tactical Maneuvers</h4>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid;\">At 14th level, you can provide leadership that allows your allies to move in perfect harmony.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: -0.8em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\">In place of moving, you can instead allow up to three allies within 30m move up to half their speed. The chosen allies must be capable of taking actions in order to move in this manner.</p>\n<h4 id=\"synchronized-assault\" style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 800; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 0.458cm; line-height: inherit; font-family: MrJeeves; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #58180d;\">Synchronized Assault</h4>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid;\">Starting at 18th level, you gain the ability to unleash a devastating combination of your allies' abilities. As a bonus action, select up to five allies within 60m. They can use their reactions to immediately take actions.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: -0.8em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\">Once you use this ability, you cannot use it again until you complete a long rest.</p>",
